Task 4: Schedule Automated Security Checks
Step 1: Create Cron Jobs
Edit crontab:

crontab -e
Add these scheduled tasks (modify paths as needed):

# Run system updates daily at 2 AM
0 2 * * * /home/student/security-automation/system-update.sh

# Run security updates daily at 3 AM
0 3 * * * /home/student/security-automation/security-update.sh

# Run security monitor every 6 hours
0 */6 * * * /usr/bin/python3 /home/student/security-automation/system_monitor.py

# Run patch manager weekly on Sundays at 4 AM
0 4 * * 0 /usr/bin/python3 /home/student/security-automation/patch_manager.py --security-only
Step 2: Verify Cron Jobs
List scheduled jobs:

crontab -l
Check cron logs:

sudo grep CRON /var/log/syslog | tail -20
Step 3: Test Manual Execution
Run scripts manually to verify:

sudo ./system-update.sh
sudo python3 system_monitor.py
sudo python3 patch_manager.py --security-only
pwsh ./windows-patch-sim.ps1
