Troubleshooting Tips
Permission Errors:

Use sudo for system-level operations
Ensure scripts have execute permissions (chmod +x)
Check log file directory permissions
Cron Jobs Not Running:

Verify cron service is active: sudo systemctl status cron
Use absolute paths in crontab entries
Check /var/log/syslog for cron errors
Ensure scripts are executable
Python Import Errors:

Install missing packages: pip3 install psutil
Verify Python version: python3 --version
Check virtual environment if used
Conclusion
This lab introduced security automation and patch management concepts through practical scripting exercises. You created Bash scripts for system updates, Python scripts for security monitoring, and PowerShell scripts for patch management simulation. You also learned to schedule automated tasks using cron jobs.

Key takeaways:

Automation reduces manual effort and human error
Regular patching is critical for security
Logging and reporting enable audit trails
Scheduled tasks ensure consistent security maintenance
Multiple scripting languages serve different purposes
Continue practicing by enhancing these scripts with additional features like email notifications, rollback capabilities, and more comprehensive security checks.
